HJR17 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 ESTABLISHING THE ALABAMA COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOOTBALL STUDY
4 COMMISSION.
5
6 WHEREAS, the Alabama Community College System (ACCS),
7 through the Alabama Community College Conference (ACCC),
8 currently supports more than 180 athletic teams across 22
9 institutions, offering opportunities to more than 2,200
10 student-athletes in sports such as baseball, basketball,
11 cross country, golf, soccer, softball, tennis, track and
12 field, volleyball, esports, and most recently, women's flag
13 football; and
14 WHEREAS, Alabama has a rich tradition and cultural
15 affinity for football, with the sport serving as a major
16 driver of community engagement, school spirit, and economic
17 activity across the state; and
18 WHEREAS, community college football programs once
19 existed in Alabama but were discontinued due to financial,
20 logistical, and administrative challenges, leaving a gap in
21 athletic opportunities for students who may not have access
22 to four-year institutions; and
23 WHEREAS, the recent success and expansion of women's
24 flag football in the ACCC, supported by legislative
25 appropriations, demonstrates the viability of introducing
26 new sports programs at the community college level; and
27 WHEREAS, reinstating football programs at community
28 colleges could provide additional pathways for
Page 1

colleges could provide additional pathways for
HJR17 Enrolled
29 student-athletes to pursue higher education, develop
30 leadership and teamwork skills, and potentially advance to
31 four-year institutions or professional opportunities; and
32 WHEREAS, a comprehensive study is needed to evaluate
33 the feasibility, costs, benefits, and potential models for
34 reintroducing football programs in Alabama's community
35 colleges; now therefore,
36 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
37 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That there is established the
38 Alabama Community College Football Study Commission to study
39 the feasibility of reinstating football programs at
40 community colleges within the Alabama Community College
41 System.
42 (a) The membership of the study commission shall
43 consist of all of the following:
44 (1) One member of the Alabama House of
45 Representatives, appointed by the Speaker of the House of
46 Representatives.
47 (2) One member of the Alabama Senate, appointed by
48 the President Pro Tempore of the Senate.
49 (3) The Chair of the House of Representatives Ways
50 and Means Education Committee, or his or her designee.
51 (4) The Chair of the Senate Finance and Taxation
52 Education Committee, or her or her designee.
53 (5) The Chancellor of the Alabama Community College
54 System, or his or her designee.
55 (6) The Commissioner of the Alabama Community College
56 Conference.
Page 2

Conference.
HJR17 Enrolled
57 (7) Two presidents of community colleges with
58 athletic programs, appointed by the Chancellor of the
59 Alabama Community College System.
60 (8) Two community college athletic directors,
61 appointed by the Commissioner of the Alabama Community
62 College Conference.
63 (9) Two high school football coaches or athletic
64 directors from high schools with a classification of 1A
65 through 5A, appointed by the Speaker of the House of
66 Representatives.
67 (10) Two high school football coaches or athletic
68 directors from high schools with a classification of 6A or
69 7A, appointed by the Senate President Pro Tempore.
70 (11) Two representatives from universities that
71 participate in the National Collegiate Athletic
72 Association's Football Bowl Subdivision appointed by the
73 Lieutenant Governor.
74 (12) Two representatives from universities that
75 participate in the Southwestern Athletic Conference,
76 appointed by a joint recommendation of the Minority Leader
77 of the House of Representatives and the Minority Leader of
78 the Senate.
79 (b) The appointing authorities shall coordinate their
80 appointments to assure the study commission membership is
81 inclusive and reflects the racial, gender, geographic,
82 urban, rural, and economic diversity of the state.
83 (c) The study commission shall have the following
84 duties:
Page 3

duties:
HJR17 Enrolled
85 (1) Assess the current infrastructure, staffing, and
86 financial capacity of the Alabama Community College
87 Conference and the institutions of Alabama Community College
88 System to implement football programs.
89 (2) Evaluate potential one-time and recurring funding
90 sources for facilities and operational costs, including
91 public-private partnerships and legislative appropriations.
92 (3) Consider models from other states with successful
93 community college football programs.
94 (4) Solicit input from stakeholders including
95 students, faculty, alumni, and local communities.
96 (5) Provide recommendations on timelines and
97 legislative actions needed to implement football in the
98 community college system.
99 (d) The first meeting of the study commission shall
100 be held no later than May 1, 2026, at which time the members
101 shall elect a chair and vice chair from among the
102 membership. The study commission may then meet as necessary
103 to conduct business.
104 (e) The Legislative Services Agency, the Clerk of the
105 House of Representatives, the Secretary of the Senate, and
106 the Alabama Community College System shall provide
107 administrative and other assistance for the work of the
108 study commission as necessary.
109 (f)(1) The legislative members of the study
110 commission shall be entitled to their legislative
111 compensation, per diem, and travel expenses for each day
Page 4

compensation, per diem, and travel expenses for each day
HJR17 Enrolled
112 they attend a meeting of the study commission pursuant to
113 Section 49 of the Constitution of Alabama 2022.
114 (2) The nonlegislative members of the study
115 commission shall serve without compensation but may be
116 reimbursed for necessary expenses in attending meetings of
117 the study commission pursuant to the policies of their
118 respective appointing authority.
119 (g) The study commission shall submit a final report
120 of its findings, conclusions, and recommendations to the
121 Governor, the Legislature, and the Chancellor of the Alabama
122 Community College System no later than November 1, 2026.
123 Upon filing its report with the Legislature, the study
124 commission shall stand dissolved and discharged of any
125 future duties and liabilities.
126 (h) Pursuant to Section 36-14-17.1, Code of Alabama
127 1975, the study commission shall provide to the Secretary of
128 State a notice of all meetings, the name of each member
129 serving on the study commission, and a copy of the final
130 report and other documents produced throughout the duration
131 of the study commission.
132 (i) Each appointing authority named herein shall be
133 provided a copy of this resolution upon its passage.
